        <updateDate>2011-10-21T20:29:56Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>American Job Creation and Investment Act of 2011 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to the election to accelerate the alternative minimum tax&nbsp;(AMT) credit in lieu of bonus depreciation, to: (1) repeal the $30 million cap on the AMT tax credit and increase the rate of such credit from 6% to 50%, (2) allow investments made by partnerships&nbsp;that are more than 50% owned by a corporation&nbsp;to qualify for such increased AMT credit amount, and (3) allow taxpayers to make separate elections for each taxable year&nbsp;to take bonus depreciation or AMT credits in lieu of&nbsp;bonus depreciation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
